      "questionText": "The master gland of the endocrine system is the:",
      "correctAnswer": "Pituitary",
      "explanation": "Why \"Pituitary\" is correct:\n- The pituitary gland is called the master gland because it controls other endocrine glands and produces hormones that regulate growth, reproduction, and metabolism.\n- It releases hormones like growth hormone (GH), thyroid-stimulating hormone (TSH), and adrenocorticotropic hormone (ACTH) that stimulate other glands.\n- Located at the base of the brain, it connects to the hypothalamus via the pituitary stalk and responds to hypothalamic releasing hormones.\n- Disorders of the pituitary can affect the entire endocrine system, causing conditions like gigantism or dwarfism.\nWhy the other options are not correct:\n- \"Thyroid\" is wrong because it produces thyroxine and regulates metabolism, but is controlled by the pituitary's TSH.\n- \"Adrenal\" is wrong because it produces cortisol and adrenaline for stress response, but is regulated by pituitary ACTH.\n- \"Pancreas\" is wrong because it produces insulin and glucagon for blood sugar control, but is not a master gland controlling others."
