      "points": 1,
      "questionText": "The period of development of the fetus in the uterus is:",
      "correctAnswer": "Gestation",
      "explanation": "Why \"Gestation\" is correct:\n- Gestation is the period of fetal development inside the mother's uterus, from implantation until birth, typically lasting about 9 months in humans.\n- During gestation, the embryo develops all major organs and systems through rapid cell division and differentiation.\n- The placenta provides nutrients, oxygen, and waste removal while protecting the fetus from harmful substances.\n- Gestation ends with labor and delivery when the fetus is mature enough to survive outside the womb.\nWhy the other options are not correct:\n- \"Ovulation\" is wrong because it is the release of a mature egg from the ovary, occurring before fertilization and implantation.\n- \"Menstruation\" is wrong because it is the monthly shedding of the uterine lining when pregnancy doesn't occur, not fetal development.\n- \"Lactation\" is wrong because it is milk production by mammary glands after birth, not the period of fetal development in the uterus."
