      "points": 1,
      "questionText": "Fruit formation without fertilization is:",
      "correctAnswer": "Parthenocarpy",
      "explanation": "Why \"Parthenocarpy\" is correct:\n- Parthenocarpy is the development of fruit without fertilization, where the ovary develops into a fruit without seeds being formed.\n- This process can occur naturally in some plants or be induced artificially to produce seedless fruits like bananas, grapes, and oranges.\n- The fruit develops normally in size and appearance but lacks viable seeds, making it advantageous for commercial fruit production.\n- Parthenocarpy is controlled by plant hormones and environmental factors, not requiring pollination or fertilization.\nWhy the other options are not correct:\n- \"Parthenogenesis\" is wrong because it is asexual reproduction where offspring develop from unfertilized eggs, common in some animals like bees.\n- \"Pollination\" is wrong because it is the transfer of pollen to the stigma, which precedes fertilization but doesn't involve fruit formation.\n- \"Germination\" is wrong because it is the process where a seed begins to sprout and grow, occurring after fertilization and seed formation."
