      "questionText": "Which of these is a non-flowering plant?",
      "correctAnswer": "Fern",
      "explanation": "Why \"Fern\" is correct:\n- Ferns are non-flowering plants that reproduce through spores instead of seeds, belonging to the group of plants called pteridophytes.\n- They have fronds (leaves) that unfurl from coiled structures and produce spores on the underside for reproduction.\n- Ferns do not produce flowers, fruits, or seeds, relying on moist environments for spore dispersal and germination.\n- They are vascular plants with well-developed roots, stems, and leaves, but lack the reproductive structures of flowering plants.\nWhy the other options are not correct:\n- \"Mango\" is wrong because it is a flowering plant that produces flowers, fruits, and seeds.\n- \"Hibiscus\" is wrong because it is a flowering plant with showy flowers and produces seeds.\n- \"Maize\" is wrong because it is a flowering plant (monocot) that produces flowers, cobs, and seeds."
