      "points": 1,
      "questionText": "Animals with backbones are:",
      "correctAnswer": "Vertebrates",
      "explanation": "Why \"Vertebrates\" is correct:\n- Vertebrates are animals that possess a backbone or spinal column made of vertebrae, which protects the spinal cord.\n- This group includes fish, amphibians, reptiles, birds, and mammals, all of which have an internal skeleton with a backbone.\n- The backbone provides structural support, protects the nervous system, and allows for greater mobility and body size.\n- Vertebrates make up only about 5% of animal species but include all large animals and most familiar ones.\nWhy the other options are not correct:\n- \"Invertebrates\" is wrong because these are animals without backbones, including insects, worms, and jellyfish.\n- \"Arthropods\" is wrong because they are a specific group of invertebrates with jointed legs and exoskeletons, like insects and spiders.\n- \"Molluscs\" is wrong because they are soft-bodied invertebrates with shells, like snails and clams, lacking backbones."
