      "points": 1,
      "questionText": "Which of these is a bryophyte?",
      "correctAnswer": "Moss",
      "explanation": "Why \"Moss\" is correct:\n- Bryophytes are small, non-vascular plants that lack true roots, stems, and leaves, and include mosses, liverworts, and hornworts.\n- Mosses absorb water and nutrients directly through their surfaces since they don't have vascular tissues like xylem and phloem.\n- They reproduce via spores and require moist environments to complete their life cycle.\n- Bryophytes are among the oldest land plants and play important roles in soil formation and moisture retention.\nWhy the other options are not correct:\n- \"Pine\" is wrong because it is a gymnosperm (conifer) with vascular tissues, seeds in cones, and woody stems.\n- \"Fern\" is wrong because it is a pteridophyte with vascular tissues and reproduces via spores, but has true roots and leaves.\n- \"Rose\" is wrong because it is an angiosperm (flowering plant) with vascular tissues, flowers, fruits, and seeds."
