      "explanation": "Why \"Botany\" is correct:\n- Botany is the scientific study of plants, including their structure, growth, reproduction, metabolism, and classification.\n- It encompasses all aspects of plant life, from microscopic algae to giant trees, and includes fields like plant physiology, taxonomy, and genetics.\n- Botanists study how plants interact with their environment and contribute to ecosystems.\n- This field is crucial for agriculture, medicine (plant-based drugs), and understanding climate change impacts on vegetation.\nWhy the other options are not correct:\n- \"Zoology\" is wrong because it is the study of animals, their behavior, physiology, and classification.\n- \"Ecology\" is wrong because it studies the relationships between organisms and their environment, including both plants and animals.\n- \"Microbiology\" is wrong because it focuses on microscopic organisms like bacteria, viruses, fungi, and protozoa."
