      "explanation": "\"faith\" is correct because the book of Romans teaches that a person is justified by faith in Jesus Christ, not by works of the law. Justification means being declared righteous before God, or being put into a right standing with Him. Paul explains that no one can earn salvation by perfect law-keeping, because all have sinned and fall short of God's standard. \"Works,\" \"law,\" and \"sacrifice\" are incorrect here because Romans does not present them as the basis of justification in the Christian message. The lesson is that salvation is received by trusting in what Christ has done, not by human effort alone."
