      "explanation": "\"exodus\" is correct because the Passover commemorates the exodus, that is, Israel's deliverance from slavery in Egypt. During the first Passover, the blood on the doorposts marked the homes of the Israelites so that judgment would pass over them. \"Creation,\" \"covenant,\" and \"sacrifice\" are related to Biblical theology in different ways, but the feast itself remembers the Exodus event. The lesson is that Passover celebrates salvation, deliverance, and God's faithfulness. Students should connect Passover with freedom and remembrance."
