      "explanation": "\"Land\" is correct because Joshua led the Israelites into the Promised Land. After Moses died, Joshua became the leader who guided the people across the Jordan and into the inheritance God had promised. \"Sea,\" \"River,\" and \"Mountain\" are wrong because the destination was the land, though rivers and mountains appear within the journey narrative. The lesson is that Joshua represents continuity in leadership and the fulfillment of God's promise. Students should remember him as the leader of entry, conquest, and settlement."
