      "explanation": "\"mother-in-law\" is correct because Ruth showed remarkable loyalty to her mother-in-law, Naomi. Even after the death of her husband, Ruth refused to abandon Naomi and chose to stay with her, saying, in effect, that Naomi's people and God would become hers. \"Husband\" cannot be correct because Ruth's husband had died. \"Children\" and \"friends\" do not capture the relationship emphasized in the story. The lesson is that Ruth models faithfulness, loyalty, and commitment even in difficult circumstances."
