      "explanation": "\"Saul\" is correct because Samuel anointed Saul as the first king of Israel. This was a major transition in Israel's history from the period of judges to monarchy. \"David\" was the second king, though he too was later anointed by Samuel. \"Solomon\" came after David, and \"Rehoboam\" belonged to an even later generation. The lesson is that Saul's story shows both the significance and the dangers of leadership without lasting obedience."
