      "explanation": "\"Goliath\" is correct because David famously defeated Goliath, the Philistine giant. The story is important not simply as a tale of bravery, but as an example of trust in God over outward strength and human intimidation. \"Saul,\" \"Absalom,\" and \"Solomon\" are people connected to David's life, but they are not the opponent in this well-known battle. The lesson is that faith in God can overcome what appears impossible. Students should connect David and Goliath with courage rooted in trust, not self-confidence alone."
