      "explanation": "\"women\" is correct because Solomon's wisdom was demonstrated in his judgment involving two women who both claimed the same child. By proposing a test that revealed the true mother's compassion, Solomon showed remarkable discernment. \"Men,\" \"children,\" and \"priests\" are incorrect because they do not describe the parties involved in that famous judgment scene. The lesson is that true wisdom includes insight into human motives, not just knowledge of laws. This story is why Solomon became widely known for wisdom."
