      "explanation": "\"Elijah\" is correct because Elisha succeeded Elijah in prophetic ministry. Before Elijah was taken up, Elisha asked for a double portion of his spirit, symbolizing a continuation of the prophetic mission. \"Isaiah,\" \"Jeremiah,\" and \"Ezekiel\" were major prophets from other contexts and did not stand in this direct succession to Elisha. The lesson is that God's work continues from one servant to another. It also teaches that spiritual leadership involves calling, preparation, and continuity."
