      "explanation": "\"John\" is correct because the four Gospels are Matthew, Mark, Luke, and John. These books present the life, teachings, death, and resurrection of Jesus from four complementary perspectives. \"Acts\" comes after the Gospels and tells the story of the early Church. \"Romans\" and \"Hebrews\" are epistles, not Gospels. The lesson is that the Gospels form the foundation of New Testament knowledge about Jesus' earthly ministry."
