      "explanation": "\"High Priest\" is correct because the book of Hebrews explains Jesus as the great High Priest. Unlike the Old Testament priests who had to offer repeated sacrifices, Jesus offered Himself once for all and opened the way to God perfectly. \"King,\" \"Prophet,\" and \"Servant\" are all true titles of Jesus in broader theology, but Hebrews especially emphasizes His priestly ministry. The lesson is that Jesus not only saves but also represents believers before God. Students should connect Hebrews with priesthood, sacrifice, and better covenant."
