      "explanation": "\"neighbor\" is correct because the Ten Commandments are commonly divided into duties to God and duties to one's neighbor. The first part focuses on worship, loyalty, reverence, and proper relation to God, while the second part focuses on human relationships such as honor, truthfulness, and respect for life and property. \"Self,\" \"church,\" and \"state\" are not the standard second division in this traditional summary. The lesson is that God's law covers both vertical relationship with God and horizontal relationship with other people. This helps students understand morality as both worship and social responsibility."
