      "correctAnswer": "disobedience",
      "explanation": "\"disobedience\" is correct because Adam and Eve were expelled from Eden after disobeying God's command not to eat from the forbidden tree. Their sin was not simply curiosity or hunger; it was a deliberate act of rebellion against God's word. \"Curiosity\" and \"hunger\" may describe feelings people can imagine in the story, but they do not capture the moral reason for the judgment. \"Tiredness\" is completely unrelated to the event. The lesson is that sin breaks fellowship with God and carries serious consequences."
