      "explanation": "\"covenant\" is correct because the rainbow was given as a sign of God's covenant after the flood. A covenant is a solemn promise or agreement, and in this case God promised never again to destroy the whole earth with a flood. \"Judgment\" is incorrect because the rainbow comes after judgment as a sign of mercy and promise. \"Mercy\" and \"power\" are true qualities of God, but the rainbow specifically represents the covenant. The lesson is that God not only judges sin, but also establishes faithful promises with humanity."
