      "explanation": "\"salt\" is correct because Lot's wife was turned into a pillar of salt after looking back toward Sodom against God's warning. Her action showed attachment to the life she was being told to leave behind. \"Stone,\" \"sand,\" and \"ash\" do not match the Biblical account. The lesson here is more than a strange event; it warns against divided loyalty and disobedience when God calls people forward. Students should remember that obedience requires trust, even when leaving the past behind is painful."
