      "explanation": "\"Aaron\" is correct because Aaron made the golden calf when the people demanded an idol while Moses was on the mountain. This was a serious act of unfaithfulness because it replaced true worship of God with image worship. \"Moses\" is wrong because he actually confronted the sin when he returned. \"Joshua\" and \"Caleb\" remained associated with faithfulness, not this act of idolatry. The lesson is that spiritual leadership must resist pressure from the crowd and remain loyal to God's command."
