      "explanation": "\"temple\" is correct because the tabernacle was a portable sanctuary or portable temple used by Israel during their wilderness journey. It was the place where God's presence was symbolically manifested among His people before the permanent temple was built. \"Palace,\" \"fortress,\" and \"city\" are wrong because the tabernacle was for worship, not government, military defense, or urban settlement. The lesson is that God chose to dwell among His people even while they were still traveling. Students should see the tabernacle as a sign of divine presence and covenant fellowship."
