      "explanation": "\"Eucharist\" is correct because the Last Supper instituted the Eucharist, also called Holy Communion or the Lord's Supper. In that meal, Jesus gave the bread and cup special meaning by connecting them to His body and blood, making the meal a lasting act of remembrance for the Church. \"Baptism\" is a different sacrament linked with entry into the Christian life, while \"Confirmation\" and \"Ordination\" belong to other church practices and were not instituted at the Last Supper. The lesson is that the Eucharist is central to Christian worship because it remembers Christ's sacrifice and celebrates covenant fellowship with Him. Students should connect the Last Supper with remembrance, sacrifice, and communion."
