      "explanation": "\"kiss\" is correct because Judas identified Jesus to the arresting crowd with a kiss. This made the betrayal especially painful because a kiss normally expresses affection, respect, or friendship, yet here it was used as a sign of treachery. \"Handshake,\" \"hug,\" and \"bow\" are wrong because they are not the action named in the Gospel account. The lesson is that betrayal often becomes more serious when trust and closeness are misused. Students should remember Judas' kiss as a symbol of outward friendliness hiding inward disloyalty."
