      "explanation": "\"innocence\" is correct because Pilate washed his hands to symbolize that he did not want to take responsibility for Jesus' death. The act was meant to show that, in his own view, he was innocent of the blood of a righteous man. \"Guilt\" is the opposite of what the action tried to express, while \"cleanliness\" and \"tradition\" do not capture the symbolic meaning of the gesture in that moment. The lesson is that symbolic actions cannot remove moral responsibility when a person still allows injustice to happen. Students should understand that Pilate's washing of hands was a sign, not a true removal of guilt."
