      "explanation": "\"Dismas and Gestas\" is correct because these are the traditional names given to the two thieves crucified with Jesus in Christian teaching. One is remembered as the repentant thief who asked Jesus to remember him, while the other remained unrepentant. \"Barabbas and Judas,\" \"Peter and John,\" and \"James and Andrew\" are all wrong because those men were different figures in the Gospel story and were not crucified beside Jesus. The lesson is that the cross reveals two different responses to Jesus: rejection and repentance. Students should focus especially on the spiritual meaning of the scene, not just the names."
