      "explanation": "\"It is finished\" is correct because these words express the completion of Jesus' earthly mission of suffering and sacrifice. They do not mean defeat; rather, they mean that the work He came to accomplish had been brought to fulfillment. \"Father forgive them,\" \"My God, my God,\" and \"Into thy hands\" are also sayings of Jesus from the cross, but they are not the one intended in this question. The lesson is that Jesus' death was purposeful and redemptive, not accidental. Students should understand this saying as a declaration of fulfillment, not despair."
