      "explanation": "\"tomb\" is correct because Joseph of Arimathea buried Jesus in his own tomb. This is important because it provided a known burial place, which later became central to the resurrection witness when the tomb was found empty. \"Garden\" is related to the area of burial, but the question asks specifically what Joseph provided, and that was his tomb. \"Cave\" and \"house\" do not match the standard wording of the Gospel account here. The lesson is that even in Jesus' burial, God's plan was moving toward resurrection and public testimony."
