      "explanation": "\"wounds\" is correct because Thomas doubted until he saw and was invited to examine Jesus' wounds. The wounds mattered because they proved that the risen Jesus was the same Jesus who had been crucified. \"Face,\" \"hands,\" and \"feet\" are not the best answers here because the issue was not merely seeing Jesus' appearance, but recognizing the marks of crucifixion. The lesson is that the resurrection was not imagination or rumor; it was grounded in real encounter with the risen Lord. Students should also note that Thomas moved from doubt to a strong confession of faith."
