      "explanation": "\"circumcised\" is correct because the Council of Jerusalem decided that Gentile believers did not need to be circumcised in order to become Christians. This decision was important because it showed that salvation comes by grace and faith, not by becoming part of the Jewish ceremonial system. \"Baptized\" is wrong because baptism remained important for believers. \"Confirmed\" and \"ordained\" are not the issue being debated in Acts 15. The lesson is that the Gospel welcomes all nations without making them first adopt every Jewish ritual practice."
