      "explanation": "\"an institution of the state\" is correct because government is the machinery or body through which the state makes and enforces decisions. In Government, the state is the larger political community, while government is the set of institutions that runs it at a particular time. \"A group of people\" is too vague because many groups exist without exercising state authority. \"A political party\" only seeks power, and \"an election process\" is just one method of choosing leaders, not government itself. The key lesson is that government is the organized authority through which the state acts."
