      "questionText": "Which of the following is a characteristic of a sovereign state?",
      "correctAnswer": "Independence",
      "explanation": "\"Independence\" is correct because a sovereign state must be free from external control. Sovereignty means supreme authority within a territory and freedom to conduct internal and external affairs without being ruled by another state. \"Dependency\" is the opposite of sovereignty because a dependent territory is controlled by another power. \"Colonialism\" describes domination, not independence, and \"Federalism\" is only a system of sharing powers within a state. The key idea is that a sovereign state must be politically independent."
