      "explanation": "Why \"Octavia Butler\" is correct:\n- Octavia Butler (1947–2006) was a pioneering American science fiction writer and the first in her genre to receive a MacArthur Fellowship (the \"Genius Grant\"). \"Kindred\" (1979) is her best-known work.\n- The novel is a unique blend of science fiction and slave narrative. It follows Dana, a modern Black woman who is repeatedly pulled back in time to a plantation in Maryland to save her white ancestor, Rufus, thus ensuring her own future existence.\n- Through this time-travel device, Butler explores the brutal realities of slavery and its enduring impact on American identity and family history.\n\nWhy the other options are not correct:\n- \"Toni Morrison\" wrote \"Beloved,\" which also deals with the legacy of slavery but in a more magical realistic/historical fiction style.\n- \"Alice Walker\" wrote \"The Color Purple.\"\n- \"Zora Neale Hurston\" wrote \"Their Eyes Were Watching God.\""
