      "correctAnswer": "If on a winter's night a traveler",
      "explanation": "Why \"If on a winter's night a traveler\" is correct:\n- Metafiction is a style of writing that self-consciously draws attention to its status as a work of art, often breaking the \"fourth wall\" between the author and the reader. Italo Calvino's \"If on a winter's night a traveler\" (1979) is a supreme example of this.\n- The novel's protagonist is actually \"You,\" the Reader, who is trying to read a book also titled \"If on a winter's night a traveler.\" The narrative is repeatedly interrupted by different opening chapters of other novels, turning the act of reading into the central theme of the book.\n- While the other options are postmodern works by Umberto Eco, they do not center on the self-referential act of reading as directly as Calvino's work.\n\nWhy the other options are not correct:\n- \"The Name of the Rose,\" \"Foucault's Pendulum,\" and \"The Island of the Day Before\" are historical and philosophical mysteries by Umberto Eco that use postmodern techniques but are not as purely metafictional in structure."
