      "explanation": "Why \"total revenue equals total cost\" is correct:\n- In economics, \"Normal Profit\" is defined as the minimum level of profit required to keep a business running in the long term. It occurs when Total Revenue (TR) is exactly equal to Total Cost (TC).\n- Note: Economic \"Total Cost\" includes opportunity costs. So, making normal profit means the owner is earning just as much as they would in their next best alternative job.\n\nWhy the other options are not correct:\n- \"total revenue exceeds total cost\" results in \"Supernormal\" or \"Abnormal\" profit.\n- \"total cost exceeds total revenue\" results in an economic loss.\n- \"marginal revenue equals marginal cost\" is the condition for *profit maximization*, but it doesn't tell you if the resulting profit is normal or supernormal."
